Supported platform:
	Linux
	Windows

License:
	libkhopper:
		LGPLv2.1 or later
	khopper_gui:
		GPLv3 or later
	plugins:
		May vary with dependencies, but basically are GPLv3

Build Dependencies:
	Toolchain (C++0x support is required):
		Windows:
			Microsoft Visual C++ 10 or later
		Linux:
			GNU Compiler Collection 4.5 or later
	Required:
		CMake:
			http://www.cmake.org/
		Qt >= 4.7 (with Phonon module): [GPL3, LGPL2.1, Commercial]
			http://qt.nokia.com/products/
		TagLib: [LGPL, MPL]
			http://developer.kde.org/~wheeler/taglib.html
	Optional:
		FFmpeg Libraries >= 0.8: [LGPL, GPL]
			http://www.ffmpeg.org/
		libFLAC >= 1.2.1: [BSD-3]
			http://flac.sourceforge.net/
		libvorbis and libogg: [BSD-3]
			http://www.xiph.org/downloads/
		LAME: [LGPL, patent]
			http://lame.sourceforge.net/

For Debian-based system users:
	# apt-get install cmake libqt4-dev libphonon-dev \
		libavcodec-dev libavformat-dev libflac-dev pkg-config \
		libvorbis-dev libmp3lame-dev libtag1-dev

Build steps:
	Linux:
		$ mkdir build
		$ cd build
		$ cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release ..
		$ make -j
	Windows:
		Please use CMake GUI to generate the building system.

Supported formats:
	Converting:
		The FFmpeg plugin will handle most formats for you, such as wav, ape ...
		Please enable the FFmpeg plugin at least or this application will has
		poor support.
	Playing:
		Any formats which are supported by plugins.

